    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-04-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-04-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="888"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d888">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48/3448a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-04-06">April 6,
                            1940</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>632. For Wayne Taylor<note n="17" xml:id="d888fn17">Wayne Chatfield Taylor,
                        American Red Cross Delegate in Paris.</note> from American Red Cross: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“As we urgently require permission to continue our shipments of medical
                            supplies and clothing to meet the desperate needs in Poland suggest you
                            endeavor secure extension present arrangement with blockade authorities
                            without awaiting decision as to foodstuffs. Quantities our supplies,
                            including innumerable articles of clothing produced by volunteers
                            throughout country, are now awaiting shipment and further delays would
                            result in great embarrassment. Gratified to know that Johnson and you
                            are proceeding through foreign office. Davis 393”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
